"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-nepal-s-first-time-participation-in-international-linguistic-olympiad\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Aug 9: Nepal participated in the International Linguistic Olympiad (IoL) for the first time in the IoL history. A team of four students from GEMS school led by Chandan Gupta, the co-organizer and co-founder of the Himalayan Computational Linguistic Olympiad, represented Nepal in the 17th International Linguistic Olympiad which was organized in Yongin, Korea from July 29 to August 2, 2019. Himal Acharya, Kushal Pathak, Umesh Yadav, and Subham Jung Karki from GEMS school got the opportunity to be part of the IoL after winning the National round of Olympiad. HCLO has been continuously organizing the linguistic olympiads at the National level since 2017, according to Gupta.  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  ANFA CEO Indraman Tuladhar said the ANFA submitted all necessary documents regarding foreign players' visas to the Ministry of Youth and Sports and the National Sports Council one and a half mon...  Nepal Republic Media Limited \\u00a9 2026.All right reserved  Nepal Republic Media Limited \\u00a9 2024. All right reserved |Privacy Policy|Terms of use 